Yobe State Governor, Hon Mai mala Buni has approved the constitution of a committee for negotiations and implementation of the new national minimum wage of N30, 000 for workers in the state. This was contained in a statement issued by the Commissioner, ministry for Information and Home Affairs, Mallam Abdullahi Bego and made available to newsmen in Damaturu. According the statement the committee will be headed by the acting Head of Service, Alhaji Muhammad Nura, the permanent secretary establishment in the office of the head of service will serve as secretary of the committee. He further said the committee is chaired by the Secretary to the Government of Yobe State, Baba Mallam Wali. The chairman and secretary of the state chapter of the Nigerian Labour Congress (NLC) as well as the chairmen of the Trade Union Congress (TUC) and the Joint Public Service negotiating Council will serve as members. Other members of the committee include the permanent secretary in charge of administration and general services in the governor’s office, and the permanent secretaries of the ministries of justice, finance and economic planning, budget and local government and chieftaincy affairs.